"I've done a lot of case competitions in my time at Schulich. You'll win some and lose some... but you gain a lot of skill and experience."
"Find your team early and get to know their strengths and weaknesses. Grow together, and in a few years you'll be killing it together."
"I'd say a good tip is to talk slow. You can communicate so much better and give yourself time to think."
"I highly recommend you learn to delegate and split things off between yourselves... Trust your team."
